cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.GR, cs.NI

The paper deals with optimizing lossy compression for a network of diverse reconstruction systems, which involves modeling displays as linear operators and formulating an operational rate-distortion optimization. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Information Theory (cs.IT), Graphics (cs.GR), or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. However, since the focus is on image compression and reconstruction, cs.MM and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories. The use of optimization techniques and standard compression methods also suggests cs.IT and cs.NI as possible sub-categories. Finally, the modeling of displays as blur degradations could also make cs.GR a relevant sub-category.
